{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772178222207,"sessionID":"ses_361f27190ffex0kTxahDpBPhcy","part":{"id":"prt_c9e0daaee001QWnuTTWWq5xfcX","sessionID":"ses_361f27190ffex0kTxahDpBPhcy","messageID":"msg_c9e0da6fd0013hMdds0qnuHcNT","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01GLHTn335Ap1omEvgjMsRcV","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/README.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Super-Ralph\n2: \n3: A unified SDLC framework for AI-assisted software development. Combines [Superpowers](https://github.com/obra/superpowers) (rigorous intake, design, review), the [OpenCode SDK](https://opencode.ai) (autonomous agent sessions), and [Beads](https://jeffreyemanuel.com) (dependency-aware task tracking with dependency-aware prioritization via `br` CLI).\n4: \n5: Every piece of work — feature, bug, refactor, hotfix — flows through the same pipeline: relentless intake, three-phase autonomous execution, embedded review, audited completion.\n6: \n7: The engine has three composable phases — **reverse**, **decompose**, and **forward** — each running the same Ralph loop (SELECT -> PROMPT -> EXECUTE -> EVALUATE) but consuming and producing different artifacts.\n8: \n9: ## Prerequisites\n10: \n11: - [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai) — AI coding agent\n12: - [bun](https://bun.sh) — JavaScript runtime\n13: - [br](https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/beads_rust) — beads CLI for task tracking\n14: \n15: ## Installation\n16: \n17: Quick install (one command):\n18: \n19: ```bash\n20: curl -fsSL \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mwarger/super-ralph/main/install.sh?$(date +%s)\" | bash\n21: ```\n22: \n23: This installer will:\n24: - install missing prerequisites (`bun`, `br`) if needed\n25: - clone/update super-ralph in `~/.super-ralph-cli`\n26: - install dependencies\n27: - install a `super-ralph` command into a writable bin directory\n28: \n29: Manual install (if you prefer):\n30: \n31: ```bash\n32: git clone https://github.com/mwarger/super-ralph.git ~/.super-ralph-cli\n33: cd ~/.super-ralph-cli && bun install\n34: ```\n35: \n36: Then add to your PATH or alias:\n37: \n38: ```bash\n39: alias super-ralph=\"bun run ~/.super-ralph-cli/src/index.ts\"\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ## Per-Project Setup\n43: \n44: ```bash\n45: super-ralph init\n46: ```\n47: \n48: Init will:\n49: 1. **Validate prerequisites** — checks that `bun` and `br` are installed, offers install commands if missing\n50: 2. **Create project files:**\n51:    - `.super-ralph/AGENTS.md` — Framework agent instructions\n52:    - `.super-ralph/forward.hbs` — Prompt template for forward phase (beads -> code)\n53:    - `.super-ralph/decompose.hbs` — Prompt template for decompose phase (spec -> beads)\n54:    - `.super-ralph/reverse.hbs` — Prompt template for reverse phase (input -> spec)\n55:    - `.super-ralph/intake-checklist.md` — Growing intake checklist\n56:    - `.super-ralph/config.toml` — Project config with auto-detected `cli.path`\n57:    - `tasks/` — Directory for generated PRDs\n58: 3. **Auto-detect `cli.path`** — resolves the absolute path to the super-ralph CLI and records it in `.super-ralph/config.toml`\n59: 4. **Initialize `.beads/` workspace** — runs `br init` if no beads workspace exists yet\n60: \n61: ## Commands\n62: \n63: ```\n64: super-ralph init                              Scaffold .super-ralph/ in current project\n65: super-ralph reverse [inputs...] [--skill ...] Input -> spec (interactive or autonomous)\n66: super-ralph decompose --spec <path>           Spec -> beads\n67: super-ralph forward --epic <ID>               Beads -> code\n68: super-ralph status --epic <ID>                Show bead progress for an epic\n69: super-ralph status --run <runId|latest>       Show run artifact status\n70: super-ralph doctor                            Preflight checks\n71: super-ralph help                              Show all options\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Common options for phase commands:\n75: - `--model <provider/model>` — Override default model for all iterations\n76: - `--max-iterations <n>` — Maximum iterations (default varies by phase)\n77: - `--dry-run` — Show what would run without executing\n78: - `--attach <url>` — Attach to existing OpenCode server instead of spawning one\n79: \n80: ## The Three-Phase Model\n81: \n82: Super-ralph is a pure Ralph loop engine with three composable phases. Each phase runs the same loop — SELECT, PROMPT, EXECUTE, EVALUATE — but consumes and produces different artifacts:\n83: \n84: ### Reverse: input -> spec\n85: \n86: ```\n87: super-ralph reverse [inputs...] [--skill ...] [--interactive] [--output <dir>]\n88: ```\n89: \n90: Takes any combination of positional inputs (files, directories, descriptions, URLs) and produces a specification. Behavior depends on what you provide:\n91: \n92: ```bash\n93: super-ralph reverse                                          # interactive interview\n94: super-ralph reverse --skill feature                          # interview with feature questions\n95: super-ralph reverse \"build a calendly clone\"                 # autonomous from description\n96: super-ralph reverse ./src/ \"refactor auth to use JWT\"        # autonomous from code + description\n97: super-ralph reverse mockup.png --interactive --skill feature # mixed: screenshot + interview\n98: ```\n99: \n100: Without inputs, runs an interactive intake interview. With inputs, runs autonomously. Use `--interactive` to force an interview even with inputs. The `--skill` flag selects a question set (feature, bug, hotfix, refactor). Output goes to `tasks/` by default.\n101: \n102: ### Decompose: spec -> beads\n103: \n104: ```\n105: super-ralph decompose --spec <path> [--epic-title <title>]\n106: ```\n107: \n108: Takes a spec/PRD file and creates beads one at a time. Each iteration, the agent reads the spec and the beads created so far, picks the next missing piece of work, creates it via `br create`, and loops. Automatically adds review, bugscan, audit, and learning beads based on config.\n109: \n110: ### Forward: beads -> code\n111: \n112: ```\n113: super-ralph forward --epic <ID>\n114: ```\n115: \n116: Takes an epic ID and implements beads. Each iteration, the orchestrator selects the highest-priority ready bead, routes it to the appropriate model, and the agent implements it, runs quality gates, commits, and closes the bead. The loop exits when no ready beads remain. Review and audit beads execute automatically at their dependency-defined points.\n117: \n118: ### Composability\n119: \n120: Each phase works standalone. They also chain:\n121: \n122: ```\n123: super-ralph reverse ./src \"rebuild auth layer\" --output docs/specs/\n124: super-ralph decompose --spec docs/specs/spec.md --epic-title \"Rebuild from spec\"\n125: super-ralph forward --epic bd-xxx\n126: ```\n127: \n128: Or enter at any point — have a PRD already? Skip to decompose. Have beads? Skip to forward.\n129: \n130: ### Completion Signaling\n131: \n132: All phases use the same `task_complete` tool with four statuses:\n133: - `{ status: \"complete\" }` — this iteration is done, loop back for the next one\n134: - `{ status: \"phase_done\" }` — the entire phase is finished, exit the loop\n135: - `{ status: \"blocked\" }` — this bead is blocked, skip and continue\n136: - `{ status: \"failed\" }` — this iteration failed, exit the loop\n137: \n138: For forward, there's a third exit condition: no ready beads means the epic is complete.\n139: \n140: ## Run Artifacts and Debugging\n141: \n142: Each phase run writes structured diagnostics under `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/`:\n143: \n144: - `session.json` — current state for this run (`running`, `completed`, `failed`), iteration counters, timestamps\n145: - `events.jsonl` — newline-delimited engine events (`iteration.started`, `iteration.completed`, `loop.completed`, etc.)\n146: - `iterations/*.log` — per-iteration transcripts with both display stream and raw event stream (when available)\n147: \n148: The latest run state is also mirrored to `.super-ralph/session.json` for quick inspection.\n149: \n150: Common checks during a long run:\n151: \n152: ```bash\n153: # watch current run state\n154: cat .super-ralph/session.json\n155: \n156: # inspect recent events from a specific run\n157: tail -n 30 .super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl\n158: \n159: # open the latest transcript\n160: ls -1t .super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations | head -n 1\n161: ```\n162: \n163: For a full artifact walkthrough, see [Run Artifacts Reference](docs/reference/run-artifacts.md).\n164: \n165: ## Model Selection\n166: \n167: Beads carry semantic `area:` labels (e.g., `area:frontend-design`, `area:backend`, `area:review`) that describe the type of work. The config maps areas to models:\n168: \n169: ```toml\n170: [models]\n171: default = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n172: \n173: [models.areas]\n174: frontend-design = \"google/gemini-2.5-pro\"\n175: backend = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n176: review = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n177: ```\n178: \n179: Resolution order:\n180: 1. CLI `--model` override (applies to all iterations in this run)\n181: 2. Bead `area:X` label -> `models.areas.X` in config\n182: 3. `models.default`\n183: \n184: Remap any area to any model/provider by editing `.super-ralph/config.toml` — no need to re-create beads.\n185: \n186: The orchestrator picks the highest-priority ready bead before creating the session, so area-based routing works in all phases including forward.\n187: \n188: ## The Pipeline (End-to-End)\n189: \n190: ### Phase 1: Planning (reverse produces specs)\n191: \n192: ```bash\n193: super-ralph reverse \"add dark mode toggle\" --skill feature\n194: ```\n195: \n196: The reverse command runs intake and design. Depending on how you invoke it:\n197: \n198: 1. **Interactive** (no inputs) — Relentless interrogation: business context, technical deep-dive, learned questions. Depth scales to skill type (feature: 10-15 questions, hotfix: 1-3).\n199: 2. **Autonomous** (with inputs) — Analyzes provided files, code, descriptions, and produces a spec directly.\n200: 3. **Mixed** (inputs + `--interactive`) — Uses inputs as context, then runs the interview for refinement.\n201: \n202: Output: a spec saved to `tasks/<name>-spec.md`.\n203: \n204: ### Phase 2: Execution (decompose + forward)\n205: \n206: ```bash\n207: super-ralph decompose --spec tasks/<name>-spec.md\n208: super-ralph forward --epic <ID>\n209: ```\n210: \n211: The super-ralph CLI runs the loop engine via the OpenCode SDK. `decompose` reads the spec and autonomously creates beads. `forward` implements beads one at a time: select (priority-sorted) -> prompt -> execute -> evaluate. Review beads execute automatically at phase boundaries. Audit beads review the entire implementation at the end. The learning bead extracts lessons and updates the intake checklist for next time.\n212: \n213: ## Updating\n214: \n215: ```bash\n216: curl -fsSL \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mwarger/super-ralph/main/install.sh?$(date +%s)\" | bash\n217: ```\n218: \n219: The installer is idempotent: it updates the existing checkout, refreshes dependencies, and re-installs the `super-ralph` wrapper.\n220: \n221: ## Uninstalling\n222: \n223: ```bash\n224: curl -fsSL \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mwarger/super-ralph/main/uninstall.sh?$(date +%s)\" | bash\n225: ```\n226: \n227: This removes the managed `super-ralph` wrapper and `~/.super-ralph-cli`.\n228: \n229: ## Design Documentation\n230: \n231: - [Three-Phase Ralph Loop Design](docs/plans/2026-02-24-three-phase-ralph-loop-design.md) — Current architecture (reverse, decompose, forward phases)\n232: - [Run Artifacts Reference](docs/reference/run-artifacts.md) — Event logs, session state, and transcript files for debugging\n233: - [Two-Phase Pipeline Design](docs/plans/2026-02-22-two-phase-pipeline-design.md) — Historical (superseded by three-phase model)\n234: - [Distribution Design](docs/plans/2026-02-21-super-ralph-distribution-design.md) — How global install works\n235: - [Original SDLC Design](docs/plans/2026-02-21-superpowers-ralph-sdlc-design.md) — Historical (superseded by two-phase pipeline)\n236: \n237: ## License\n238: \n239: MIT\n\n(End of file - total 239 lines)\n</content>","title":"README.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Super-Ralph\n\nA unified SDLC framework for AI-assisted software development. Combines [Superpowers](https://github.com/obra/superpowers) (rigorous intake, design, review), the [OpenCode SDK](https://opencode.ai) (autonomous agent sessions), and [Beads](https://jeffreyemanuel.com) (dependency-aware task tracking with dependency-aware prioritization via `br` CLI).\n\nEvery piece of work — feature, bug, refactor, hotfix — flows through the same pipeline: relentless intake, three-phase autonomous execution, embedded review, audited completion.\n\nThe engine has three composable phases — **reverse**, **decompose**, and **forward** — each running the same Ralph loop (SELECT -> PROMPT -> EXECUTE -> EVALUATE) but consuming and producing different artifacts.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai) — AI coding agent\n- [bun](https://bun.sh) — JavaScript runtime\n- [br](https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/beads_rust) — beads CLI for task tracking\n\n## Installation\n\nQuick install (one command):\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mwarger/super-ralph/main/install.sh?$(date +%s)\" | bash","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772178222193,"end":1772178222206}}}}
