{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772178231537,"sessionID":"ses_361f27190ffex0kTxahDpBPhcy","part":{"id":"prt_c9e0dceb0001uDvMPTfBIdzh88","sessionID":"ses_361f27190ffex0kTxahDpBPhcy","messageID":"msg_c9e0dc3ef001Jx5r6A8lZVoYnJ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_011g2n9UkS5c7MGHjpToxFHG","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/docs/reference/ralph-loop-architecture.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/docs/reference/ralph-loop-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Ralph Loop Architecture — Reference Documentation\n2: \n3: > Technical reference for understanding the ralph-tui execution loop and how to\n4: > build an OpenCode SDK-based equivalent. This is research documentation, not an\n5: > implementation plan.\n6: \n7: ## Source\n8: \n9: All analysis is based on `github.com/subsy/ralph-tui` (MIT License, v0.10.0).\n10: Key files: `src/engine/index.ts` (2,283 lines), `src/engine/types.ts` (~530 lines),\n11: `src/plugins/agents/types.ts` (~330 lines), `src/plugins/trackers/types.ts` (~310 lines),\n12: `src/templates/engine.ts` (~470 lines).\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## The Loop (simplified)\n17: \n18: The entire ralph-tui execution model reduces to this:\n19: \n20: ```\n21: while (!shouldStop):\n22:     if paused: poll every 100ms until resumed\n23:     if on fallback agent: attempt primary agent recovery\n24:     if currentIteration >= maxIterations: stop(max_iterations)\n25:     if tracker.isComplete(): stop(completed)\n26:     \n27:     task = getNextAvailableTask()   // dependency-aware, skips completed\n28:     if !task: stop(no_tasks)\n29:     \n30:     try:\n31:         result = runIteration(task)\n32:     catch:\n33:         if strategy == retry && retries < max: retry with backoff\n34:         if strategy == skip: add to skippedTasks, continue\n35:         if strategy == abort: break\n36:     \n37:     updateSession(currentIteration)\n38:     sleep(iterationDelay)           // default 1000ms\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ## Single Iteration\n42: \n43: ```\n44: 1. Increment iteration counter\n45: 2. Set task status to in_progress via tracker\n46: 3. Build prompt:\n47:    a. Load recent progress (last 5 iterations from progress.md)\n48:    b. Load codebase patterns (from progress.md)\n49:    c. Get PRD context from tracker (if available)\n50:    d. Get template (5-level hierarchy: custom > project > global > tracker > builtin)\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 340. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","title":"docs/reference/ralph-loop-architecture.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Ralph Loop Architecture — Reference Documentation\n\n> Technical reference for understanding the ralph-tui execution loop and how to\n> build an OpenCode SDK-based equivalent. This is research documentation, not an\n> implementation plan.\n\n## Source\n\nAll analysis is based on `github.com/subsy/ralph-tui` (MIT License, v0.10.0).\nKey files: `src/engine/index.ts` (2,283 lines), `src/engine/types.ts` (~530 lines),\n`src/plugins/agents/types.ts` (~330 lines), `src/plugins/trackers/types.ts` (~310 lines),\n`src/templates/engine.ts` (~470 lines).\n\n---\n\n## The Loop (simplified)\n\nThe entire ralph-tui execution model reduces to this:\n\n```","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772178231528,"end":1772178231536}}}}
