{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772178399233,"sessionID":"ses_361f27190ffex0kTxahDpBPhcy","part":{"id":"prt_c9e105c94001Za0otIE3HWw9qq","sessionID":"ses_361f27190ffex0kTxahDpBPhcy","messageID":"msg_c9e1058d1001Jk4yB5IuPjKNYx","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01TooGH6tZrnJtGc5nbsRoVY","tool":"bash","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"vale --version && vale --help 2>&1 | head -30","description":"Check vale version and help"},"output":"vale version 3.13.1\nvale - A command-line linter for prose.\n\n\u001b[1mUsage\u001b[0m:\t\u001b[2mvale [options] [input...]\u001b[0m\n\t\u001b[2mvale myfile.md myfile1.md mydir1\u001b[0m\n\t\u001b[2mvale --output=JSON [input...]\u001b[0m\n\nVale is a syntax-aware linter for prose built with speed and extensibility in\nmind. It supports Markdown, AsciiDoc, reStructuredText, HTML, and more.\n\nTo get started, you'll need a configuration file (\u001b[2m.vale.ini\u001b[0m):\n\n\u001b[1mExample\u001b[0m:\n\n\t\u001b[2mMinAlertLevel = suggestion\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2m\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2m\t[*]\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2m\tBasedOnStyles = Vale\u001b[0m\n\nSee \u001b[4mhttps://vale.sh\u001b[0m for more setup information.\n\u001b[1m\u001b[0m\n\u001b[1mFlags:\u001b[0m\n\n \u001b[2m--config\u001b[0m         A file path (\u001b[2m--config='some/file/path/.vale.ini'\u001b[0m).    \n \u001b[2m--ext\u001b[0m            An extension to associate with stdin (\u001b[2m--ext=.md\u001b[0m).     \n \u001b[2m--filter\u001b[0m         An expression to filter rules by.                     \n \u001b[2m--glob\u001b[0m           A glob pattern (\u001b[2m--glob='*.{md,txt}.'\u001b[0m)                 \n \u001b[2m-h\u001b[0m, \u001b[2m--help\u001b[0m       Print this help message.                              \n \u001b[2m--ignore-syntax\u001b[0m  Lint all files line-by-line.                          \n \u001b[2m--minAlertLevel\u001b[0m  The minimum level to display (\u001b[2m--minAlertLevel=error\u001b[0m). \n \u001b[2m--no-exit\u001b[0m        Don't return a nonzero exit code on errors.           \n","title":"Check vale version and help","metadata":{"output":"vale version 3.13.1\nvale - A command-line linter for prose.\n\n\u001b[1mUsage\u001b[0m:\t\u001b[2mvale [options] [input...]\u001b[0m\n\t\u001b[2mvale myfile.md myfile1.md mydir1\u001b[0m\n\t\u001b[2mvale --output=JSON [input...]\u001b[0m\n\nVale is a syntax-aware linter for prose built with speed and extensibility in\nmind. It supports Markdown, AsciiDoc, reStructuredText, HTML, and more.\n\nTo get started, you'll need a configuration file (\u001b[2m.vale.ini\u001b[0m):\n\n\u001b[1mExample\u001b[0m:\n\n\t\u001b[2mMinAlertLevel = suggestion\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2m\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2m\t[*]\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2m\tBasedOnStyles = Vale\u001b[0m\n\nSee \u001b[4mhttps://vale.sh\u001b[0m for more setup information.\n\u001b[1m\u001b[0m\n\u001b[1mFlags:\u001b[0m\n\n \u001b[2m--config\u001b[0m         A file path (\u001b[2m--config='some/file/path/.vale.ini'\u001b[0m).    \n \u001b[2m--ext\u001b[0m            An extension to associate with stdin (\u001b[2m--ext=.md\u001b[0m).     \n \u001b[2m--filter\u001b[0m         An expression to filter rules by.                     \n \u001b[2m--glob\u001b[0m           A glob pattern (\u001b[2m--glob='*.{md,txt}.'\u001b[0m)                 \n \u001b[2m-h\u001b[0m, \u001b[2m--help\u001b[0m       Print this help message.                              \n \u001b[2m--ignore-syntax\u001b[0m  Lint all files line-by-line.                          \n \u001b[2m--minAlertLevel\u001b[0m  The minimum level to display (\u001b[2m--minAlertLevel=error\u001b[0m). \n \u001b[2m--no-exit\u001b[0m        Don't return a nonzero exit code on errors.           \n","exit":0,"description":"Check vale version and help","truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772178399052,"end":1772178399233}}}}
